description.plain:
D’Anthony Carlos (May 17th, 1993), better known by his stage name GoldLink, is an American rapper from Washington, DC.

He is a new wave artist from the DMV who incorporates elements of Hip-Hop, R&B and House in a sub-genre he has dubbed as Future Bounce.

Rising to prominence on Soundcloud, GoldLink released his debut mixtape The God Complex through his own label, squaaash club, in 2014 to much critical acclaim; many cited the biographical nature as a highlight. Riding off the success of the mixtape, GoldLink would join the independent collective, Soulection, under which he would release his sophomore project And After That, We Didn’t Talk (released 2015); which eventually landed him a deal with RCA.

On December 16th, 2016, GoldLink dropped “Crew,” to build anticipation for his upcoming mixtape At What Cost. The releases of “Meditation”   (March 9th, 2017) and “Pray Everyday (Survivor’s Guilt)” (March 17th, 2017), which were also dropped to build anticipation for the album. On the March 24th, 2017, GoldLink released At What Cost.

On June 12th, 2019, GoldLink released his debut album, DIASPORA

description.plain:
“Crew” was the 1st and most successful of 3 tracks — the other two being “Meditation” and “Pray Everyday (Survivor’s Guilt)” — that were dropped as singles to build anticipation for the album.

Goldlink’s collab with D.C artists Shy Glizzy—now Young Jefe—and Brent Faiyaz to create this track was described by XXL as:

perfectly blend[ing] each artist's’ unique styles into one awesome party record

description.plain:
D.C. and Atlanta combine to extend an already phenomenal track in “Crew”. After earning a gold plaque for his effort with the original track, Goldlink applies more pressure for the capital state with the addition of Gucci Mane.

On this track, the four rappers take turns bragging about their material possessions and flex their blessings.
